id: pmc-91po
title: Audit git history for private data exposure
description: "Review every commit reachable from all refs for credential-like literals, private key filenames, env files, and other secret-bearing artifacts before public release."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[3]: history,release,security
created_at: "2026-05-23T19:19:07.254Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T19:22:50.153Z"
deadline: "2026-05-23T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "- Full reachable git history is scanned, not only the working tree.\n- Any confirmed private data finding is remediated before release.\n- Synthetic security test fixtures are documented as false positives.\n- Final release notes record the secret scan result."
parent: pmc-ysps
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: 0.1.0
reporter: codex
severity: high
environment: local git repository all refs
repro_steps: Run git grep over git rev-list --all and enumerate historical filenames for secret-bearing patterns.
resolution: Completed full reachable-history secret scan and filename audit; no confirmed private data was found.
expected_result: "All commits reachable from every ref contain no private credentials, private keys, env files, or secret-bearing artifacts."
actual_result: "Pattern scan matched only sanitizer code that clears URL passwords and a synthetic test fixture URL containing token=secret; historical filename audit returned no env, key, credential, token, or secret files."
component: repository-security
